This paper discusses the ELM method, which is commonly used in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses incremental methods for solving the pseudoinverse, which is a common problem in neural networks and falls under the category of optimization. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the accuracy and adaptability of the solution, which are important aspects of artificial intelligence and computer vision, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper discusses the ease of computation, which is a common concern in systems and control, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
